      h3(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/list-view-links.html") Link Elements
      p Of course in most cases we need to use list view elements as links (&lt;a&gt;) to other pages or data. In this case we need to wrap "item-content" with &lt;a class="item-link"&gt; element:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;a href="#" class="item-link"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="item-content"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="item-media"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="item-inner"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/a&gt;          
      p If your links contains nothing except "item-content" then we can just use link as "item-content":
      pre
        code
          | &lt;a href="#" class="item-link item-content"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="item-media"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="item-inner"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/a&gt; 
      p 
        strong Note that "item-inner" has additional right padding and chevron icon when it is in "item-link"
      h4 Example
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="list-block"&gt;
          |   &lt;ul&gt;
